The Coronation: Kings Landing will a showcase of hip-hop music aimed at re-instating and re-introducing hip-hop to the Nigerian music scene. Hosted by 100 Crowns, the night will feature performances from the next best and hottest young hip-hop acts and some of the biggest rap acts in the country. “The Coronation: Kings Landing” is aimed at showing the future of hip-hop in Nigeria. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-708538 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3.jpg" alt="" width="1080" height="1080" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3.jpg 1080w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-598x598.jpg 598w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-100x100.jpg 100w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-200x200.jpg 200w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-487x487.jpg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-974x974.jpg 974w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-240x240.jpg 240w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-480x480.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Coronation-3-600x600.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px" /> This edition is headlined MI Abaga and features A-Q, Terry Apala, Ms Kizz, Blaqbonez, Teeto Ceemos, Uzi, Eclipse Nkasi, DDTM, Joules Da Kid, Hench, Straffitti, Cameey, Bid Daddy Jay, Street Billionairees, East Sidaz, Dj Walk It, Dan Dizzy, Crinerry, Shakes, Reespect, Holyfield. The vision of the coronation is to become the standard in hip-hop concerts in Nigeria and Africa as a whole by channelling hip-hop through the African lens. Date: Saturday 4th August 2018 Time: 7:00 p.m Venue: Silverbird Galleria ENTRY IS FREE